ARI (Adjusted Rand Index) is a measure of the similarity between two data clusterings; 
AMI (Adjusted Mutual Information) is a measure of the mutual information between two clusterings, adjusted for chance; 
NMI (Normalized Mutual Information) is a measure of the mutual information between two clusterings, normalized by their joint entropy; 
MI (Mutual Information) is a measure of the mutual dependence between two variables; 
Homogeneity score is a measure of the homogeneity of a clustering, i.e., whether each cluster contains only members of a single class; 
Completeness score is a measure of the completeness of a clustering, i.e., whether all members of a given class are assigned to the same cluster.
